About this Script

This script is a rock, paper, scisor game created with python.

How to use

To use this script, you need to have python installed on your computer. You can download it here.

After you have installed python, you can run the script by opening the terminal and typing:

python rock_paper_scissors.py

The script will ask you to choose between rock, paper or scissors. You can type your choice and press enter. The script will then choose a random choice and compare it to yours. It will then tell you if you won, lost or if it was a draw.

You can play as many times as you want. To stop the script, you can press ctrl + c.



